OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FBurundi floods: Lake       
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25FTanganyika's water levels  
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Frise                       
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Natural disasters have forced more than
OL,6, 100,000 people to flee their homes in  
OL,7, Burundi in recent years, the Save the  
OL,8, Children charity says.                 
OL,10,FMost of them had lived on the shores of
OL,11,FLake Tanganyika where water levels had 
OL,12,Frisen because of heavy storms, causing 
OL,13,Ffloods and landslides.                 
OL,15,FPeople described waking up at night to 
OL,16,Ffind their homes and farms swallowed by
OL,17,Fthe lake, the world's second-deepest.  
OL,19,FSave the Children said it was the      
OL,20,F"forgotten crisis".                    
